## Documentation Audiences

This repo follows [ai-human-docs](https://github.com/modern-tooling/ai-human-docs).

Before editing any documentation file, check for `<!-- doc-audience: ... -->` on line 1.

| Tag | Meaning |
|-----|---------|
| `<!-- doc-audience: human, preserve-voice -->` | Human doc. **DO NOT** edit, expand, or rephrase. |
| `<!-- doc-audience: human, ai-editable -->` | Human doc. May edit, but preserve concise voice. |
| `<!-- doc-audience: ai -->` | AI doc. Edit freely, be verbose and explicit. |

**Default behavior:** If no tag present, check the directory:
- `docs/human/` - Treat as `human, preserve-voice`
- `docs/ai/` - Treat as `ai`
- Other locations - Ask before editing

**Commit messages:** When editing docs, list which files you edited:
```
Docs edited:
- path/to/file.md (ai)
```
